tribution metrics at commit time.\\n   479→// This is a point-in-time snapshot comparing the checkpoint tree (agent work)\\n   480→// against the committed tree (may include human edits).\\n   481→//\\n   482→// Attribution Metrics:\\n   483→//   - TotalCommitted measures \\\"net additions\\\" (lines added that remain in the commit)\\n   484→//   - AgentPercentage represents \\\"of the new code added, what percentage came from the agent\\\"\\n   485→//   - Deletion work is tracked separately in HumanRemoved (not included in percentage)\\n   486→//\\n   487→// Deletion-Only Commits:\\n   488→// For commits with only deletions (no additions), TotalCommitted will be 0 and\\n   489→// AgentPercentage will be 0. This is by design - the percentage metric is only\\n   490→// meaningful for commits that add code. Deletion contributions are captured in\\n   491→// the HumanRemoved field but don't affect the attribution percentage.\\n   492→type InitialAttribution struct {\\n   493→\\tCalculatedAt    time.Time `json:\\\"calculated_at\\\"`\\n   494→\\tAgentLines      int       `json:\\\"agent_lines\\\"`      // Lines added by agent (base → shadow diff)\\n   495→\\tHumanAdded      int       `json:\\\"human_added\\\"`      // Lines added by human (excluding modifications)\\n   496→\\tHumanModified   int       `json:\\\"human_modified\\\"`   // Lines modified by human (estimate: min(added, removed))\\n   497→\\tHumanRemoved    int       `json:\\\"human_removed\\\"`    // Lines removed by human (excluding modifications)\\n   498→\\tTotalCommitted  int       `json:\\\"total_committed\\\"`  // Net additions in commit (agent + human new lines, not total file size)\\n   499→\\tAgentPercentage float64   `json:\\\"agent_percentage\\\"` // agent_lines / total_committed * 100 (0 for deletion-only commits)\\n   500→}\\n   501→\\n   502→// Info provides summary information for listing checkpoints.\\n   503→// This is the generic checkpoint info type.\\n   504→type Info struct {\\n   505→\\t